### @nuance・23 SuperEnsemble Added - Incentivizing Specialization for Greater General Capability

### Overview of the Image SuperEnsemble
We just merged a groundbreaking update called the Image SuperEnsemble.

The SuperEnsemble starts out with two categories: General and Digital Art.

Each category receives prompts in line with the category, incentivizing miners to run models specialized on that type of prompts.

With time, we will add more and more categories, and subcategories, incentivizing specialization amongst miners.

Alongside this we are building a prompt classifier that can map prompts to the right category, subcategory and even miner, in order to get the best possible result.

### Benefits of the SuperEnsemble

Currently almost all APIs, related to Bittensor or not, are mapping directly to one model.

With the SuperEnsemble, instead of running a single model, miners are incentivized to specialize in different categories, or "Niches", to get better results for that specific Niche.

Then, when someone send an organic request through the API, a classifier channels the request to the miner that will likely give the best response for that specific prompt.

Some example categories for specialization include: Digital art, landscape, humans, realistic, anime.

For each of these categories, highly specialized models exists, that gives better results than general models.

### Why the SuperEnsemble Works Perfectly with Bittensor

The SuperEnsemble needs specialized models, and the more people that can add models, the greater number of specialized models can be added to improve the SuperEnsemble.

Therefore Bittensor has a huge advantage compared to centralized APIs, where the company itself has to develop big number of models.

### Emission Change

We are moving 1% emission each from AnimeV3 and REXL, and adding to the two new SuperEnsemble categories: OpenGeneral and OpenDigitalArt
